Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104iei1665702682832.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iei1665702682832.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iei1665702682832.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"iei1665702682832\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Cryptographic Hash Functions\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"iei1665702682832__cryptographic_hash_functions_125482\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Cryptographic hash functions take a string of any length as input and produce a fixed-length hash value. This can be used to verify and authenticate data because any change to the source produces a very different hash value. They are used for information security applications, such as digital signatures and message authentication codes.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iei1665702682832__p_d40190e1_d40191e1_d40192e1\">Other encryption and signature algorithms use hash functions in combination with symmetric or asymmetric keys to provide more secure data protection.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Supported Hash Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">Algorithm</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">MD4</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\"> MD4 (Message Digest 4) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">MD5</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\"> MD5 (Message Digest 5) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SHA1</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\"> SHA-1 (Secure Hash Algorithm 1) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SHA224</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\">SHA-224 (Secure Hash Algorithm 224 bit) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SHA256</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\">SHA-256 (Secure Hash Algorithm 256 bit) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SHA384</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\">SHA-384 (Secure Hash Algorithm 384 bit) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SHA512</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iei1665702682832__table_d3905e1_d3906e1_d3907e1__entry__2\">SHA-512 (Secure Hash Algorithm 512 bit) </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Cryptographic Hash Functions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Cryptographic Hash Functions Cryptographic hash functions take a string of any length as input and produce a fixed-length hash value. This can be used to verify and authenticate data because any change to the source produces a very different hash value. They are used for information security applications, such as digital signatures and message authentication codes. Other encryption and signature algorithms use hash functions in combination with symmetric or asymmetric keys to provide more secure data protection. Table 1. Supported Hash Functions Algorithm Meaning MD4 MD4 (Message Digest 4) MD5 MD5 (Message Digest 5) SHA1 SHA-1 (Secure Hash Algorithm 1) SHA224 SHA-224 (Secure Hash Algorithm 224 bit) SHA256 SHA-256 (Secure Hash Algorithm 256 bit) SHA384 SHA-384 (Secure Hash Algorithm 384 bit) SHA512 SHA-512 (Secure Hash Algorithm 512 bit) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}